1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with delay bounds in networking, specifically in deterministic and time-sensitive networking. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses arrival and service curve characterizations to prove delay bounds, which is a concept related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with bounding delays in a system, which is a concept related to systems and control. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with delay bounds in a network, which is a concept related to distributed computing. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - Although less likely, the paper may also be related to programming languages as it deals with formal proofs of delay bounds using network calculus.
